## Leader
The Leader element can be used to fill horizontal space between two inline elements with special characters, blank space or other elements. It is typically used when creating a Table of Contents or dotted lines for signatures.

The width of the space can either be specified manually, or set to use the maximum width available on the element’s line (*default*).

The Leader type determines the filling of the space:

- **space**: Blank space

- **rule**: Underscores

- **dots**: Periods

- **use-content**: Fills the space with the content of a child element of the Leader

> Note

For more information, please refer to the [W3C documentation](https://www.w3.org/TR/2001/REC-xsl-20011015/xslspec.html#fo_leader) of the Leader element.

## Wrapper
The Wrapper element is used to define and propagate FO properties to its children elements. It doesn’t generate any areas and doesn’t use the properties assigned to it (except for id).

To nestle an existing element into a Wrapper, right-click on the element in Outline and select *Wrap with… *&gt; *Wrapper*. A parent element Wrapper is created.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

A Wrapper may only contain elements which can also be children of its parent element, including other Wrapper elements.

> Note

For more information, please refer to the [W3C documentation](https://www.w3.org/TR/2001/REC-xsl-20011015/xslspec.html#fo_wrapper) of the Wrapper element.
